scene.message:
Clerk: They say the customer{nl}
is god. You seem to be a{nl}
customer. Therefore,{waitkey}you must be a god.{waitkey}{clearbox}Please! Put the town back to{nl}
normal! I can't restock, and{nl}
it's a real problem.{waitkey}{ret}

Townsperson: I'd felt for a{nl}
while that something was off{nl}
about this town.{waitkey}{clearbox}Maybe this upheaval happening{nl}
was for the best.{waitkey}{ret}

Maki: The upheaval being for{nl}
the best... that's true, isn't{nl}
it.{waitkey}If not for it, I... wouldn't{nl}
have known a thing.{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: Restock, you say? Come{nl}
to think of it, where does{nl}
this town's merchandise come{nl}
from?{waitkey}Well, no use pondering it.{waitkey}{ret}

Reiji: We've no business in a{nl}
place like this.{waitkey}Honestly... whether you've{nl}
got guts or you're just a{nl}
fool... I can't make you out.{waitkey}Well, one thing's certain —{nl}
you're an interesting one.{waitkey}{ret}
